---
// MCPSection.astro — dark "Claude drives it" band with a real MCP call sample.
---
<section id="mcp" class="mt-[104px] bg-night text-ink-100">
  <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-[1180px] grid-cols-1 items-center gap-14 px-6 py-[84px] sm:px-8 md:grid-cols-2">
    <div>
      <div class="font-mono text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-teal-400">Model Context Protocol</div>
      <h2 class="mt-3.5 text-[clamp(28px,5vw,38px)] font-bold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] text-white">
        Claude drives it.<br />Right from your editor.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-[18px] max-w-[460px] text-[16px] leading-[1.6] text-[#aebcc9]">
        <span class="font-mono text-white">graph-read mcp</span> exposes the graph as MCP tools. Point
        Claude Code or Claude Desktop at it and the model reasons over your live topology — reviewing a
        PR, planning a migration, or running an incident — citing the exact entities and edges it walked.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-[26px] flex flex-wrap gap-x-[22px] gap-y-2 font-mono text-[12.5px] text-[#8aa0b2]">
        <span><span class="text-teal-400">▹</span> search</span>
        <span><span class="text-teal-400">▹</span> get_subgraph</span>
        <span><span class="text-teal-400">▹</span> list_flows</span>
        <span><span class="text-teal-400">▹</span> get_flow</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[14px] border border-night-line bg-night-2 shadow-[0_20px_50px_-20px_rgba(0,0,0,.5)]">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-[7px] border-b border-night-line px-3.5 py-[11px]">
        <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-night-edge"></span>
        <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-night-edge"></span>
        <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-night-edge"></span>
        <span class="ml-1.5 font-mono text-[11px] text-[#6b8499]">claude · mcp call</span>
      </div>
      <pre class="m-0 overflow-x-auto px-[18px] pb-5 pt-[18px] font-mono text-[12.5px] leading-[1.7] text-[#c4d2dd]"><span class="text-[#5e7488]">&gt; What breaks if I take down auth-service?</span>

<span class="text-teal-400">get_subgraph</span>(<span class="text-[#e6b673]">"deployment:prod/auth-service"</span>)
  <span class="text-[#5e7488]"># walk callers (CALLED_BY)</span>

<span class="text-[#5e7488]">→ 7 services break — 3 direct, 4 transitive ✓</span></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
